1 olive oil
1 bag baby spinach leaves
½ lemon
1 tin sweetcorn
1 bag slaw mix
1 packet garlic aioli
1 packet pulled chicken
1 packet Peri Peri Sauce
6 Mini Flour Tortillas
1 packet sour cream
1 bag coriander
1 sachet All-American Spice Blend
1 packet Shredded Cheddar Cheese

• Roughly chop spinach. Cut lemon in
half. Drain the corn
• In a bowl, combine slaw mix,
spinach, corn, aioli and a squeeze of
lemon juice. Season

• Discard liquid from pulled chicken
packaging
• Heat oil in a frying pan over
medium-high heat
• Cook chicken and spice blend,
breaking up, until browned, 2-3 mins
• Remove pan from heat and add peri
peri sauce, tossing, until combined,
30 seconds

• Microwave tortillas on a plate in
10 second bursts until warmed
through
• Top tortillas with slaw, chicken, sour
cream, cheese and coriander. Serve
with remaining lemon wedges